snippet.textDisplay:
Reasons for cancellation of final year exams and promoting final year students. 
1.	Health issue of students is the biggest concern. Government and UGC may claim that social distancing will be maintained in examination halls but how can they ensure safety of all the students in their hostel rooms or rented rooms? 3-4 people share a room, how can they ensure safety of students there? Also we have to go out for food or other necessities, how can safety be maintained there? Many local students will also travel in public transportation everyday to come to give exams and if they get infected and remain asymptomatic for days and keep on infecting people and also themselves fall sick and their family members also becomes infected. Who will take responsibility of their life? Also in cities the numbers of cases e raising each and every day and lockdown is being imposed in various parts every other week, so if a student is from that area that has been affected the most how will anyone travel from that place and come to give the exam? The student may have given 3-4 exams but suddenly his locality or society comes under contaminated zone how will he travel to give the exams and what amount of mental pressure will he have to undergo? And also how will so many students be able to travel to different states in the middle of a pandemic and so many have left their rented houses how will they get a house for rent in the middle of a pandemic and that too for 1-2 months? Government is not looking at other problems and just telling about social distancing in the exam centre and nothing else. 


2.	Will government give a written declaration that they will take full responsibility of student’s health and if they get infected Covid19? Can government give a written statement that they will take care of our hospital bill which reaches lakhs of rupees and also will appoint officials in every college to find hospital beds or quarantine centre for students if they gets infected?  Because we will not have our guardian or parents in other states and we will also no be able to home quarantine because we live in hostels and PGs on sharing basis and staying in infected condition will make others staying with us prone to infection too.


3.	Now many people are also preparing for competitive exams for jobs or entrance exams for higher studies. Maybe the exams will not get conducted now but we can at least start preparing for them, if we remain stuck with our college exams how will we prepare for those exams with so much of uncertainty? Also many people have got jobs through campus placements and will require a degree to join their jobs by July or September, if they cannot provide the degree and will lose their jobs. How is government planning to compensate for that? Now some people may tell so you can join your job and travel for your job but you cannot travel for exams and sit for exams? So let me explain most of the work places are working with 25% -40% of work force or employees and rest are working from home. And in some places most of the people are working from home. So social distance is possible and it is not that dangerous. And if their locality comes under contamination zone or that person falls sick he/she can take leave and stay at home which is not the case with exams because if a person will get stuck in a contaminated zone he/she will miss the exams and will be pushed into a darkness of uncertainty. Also unlike jobs exams will require mental focus day and night for a continuous period of 2-3 weeks which is not possible at al in the current situation.

4.	 Now coming to online exams, online exams and OBE are in no way judging the merit of the students as people will look for the answers from somewhere else and write the answers. Someone from UGC said so many people cheat in regular exams so does that mean we should stop regular exams too? Let me explain, in a regular exam there are teachers present in the examination centre to check if students are using any mal practices and maybe less than 1% students’ passes exams by cheating. Now everyone will just write answers from book. How will it judge the merits of the students? Is it not better to evaluate on their past performances and internal marks? And also most of the students don’t have a laptop with them and internet connection is  not so good in rural areas, how is it even fair for the students not having all these? UGC is telling students who will not be able to write exams now can write it later when everything gets normal which is a very uncertain amount of time. For example my friend has a laptop and access to fast internet connections will be able to give exams now and pass and as i live in a rural area and don’t have access to the above stated thing, i will have to wait for an uncertain amount of time to get my degree. Till then my whole career will be on hold? How is this even fair. And many technical courses have practical exams how will they give practical exams online?

5.	Now coming to why we are demanding to promote final year students. We never demanded promoting of final year students without exams till June. But govt promoted all school students based on previous year’s performance. Govt promoted 12 ad 10 students based on pre board marks and other internal assessment marks, where as in 10 and 12 pre board papers are not even checked by respective boards and in class 10 and 12 actually the final years marks is required to get admission in any college but still they were promoted based on previous marks. Now coming to the college semester system, the semester exam was brought in so that student’s merit is not only judged on the final year exam but through various internal exams or mid-term exams, and if other intermediate semester students can be promoted based on their previous semester marks and internal marks why not the final semester students? Why only discrimination with final year students?? When they will graduate after 1 year or 2 years they too will have given one semester less so how will their degrees be valid and our degrees invalid or corona degree or corona batch? Also if we apply for jobs the final year marks in not asked separately but an average marks of all the semesters. And those who get jobs through placements they get their jobs way before final exam and they just have to pass the exams and get a degree. And for other entrance exams for higher studies or jobs we have to clear the entrance exams designed by them also they take into consideration the average percentage of all the semester in exams, not only of the final year marks. So this reason that if we don’t give the final semester exams our degrees will be of no use or our jobs and career will get impacted is completely an absurd reason. Like other semester students has been promoted we can also be promoted.

6.	The government could have easily declared this year as zero year and paid at least the basic salaries to the college staff and professors from its emergency and disaster funds, but they didn’t do it because they don’t want to spend money on education. If all of the education system was held for 1 year due to this unforeseen situation it would not have been a big issue, but govt didn’t do it. If this pandemic continues for another year will govt keep on educating everyone through online medium? Will it not mean that education is being imparted to only the privileged ones? Keeping our degrees on hold is just putting our career on hold and destroying our future and forcing the students to give offline exams is just putting millions students to death and i have already told the problems with online exams in the points above. So it is our demand to promote final year students based on their previous semester and internal semester exam and make our degrees available to us as soon as possible. Thankyou.

snippet.textDisplay:
Malnutrition as defined by westerners may not be fully applicable in India. The definitions of nutrition and malnutrition are picked up by Indians from western countries. In our country, studies on nutrition and malnutrition from keeping Indian context and thinking in mind are far and few. Most research is in accordance with the western criteria..
Second point is that, urban and semi urban Indian population is heavily influenced by the western style of food habits which is not suitable to us  physically and environmentally.
Our ancestors were very far sighted and hence developed a very balanced vegetarian diet but we left it because of the slavery mindset.
Excessive non veg diet, excessive alcohol consumption, excessive street food and baked products are the influential factors in increasing obesity. In addition hybrid food, grains is also an important factor. Another point is of the use of chemical fertilizers in farming. Chemical fertilizers and pesticides even in minute quantities accumulate in cells and interfere in the normal metabolism. Hybrid food is always lesser in quality than the natural original variety. 
This is a very serious situation. Unfortunately politics ruins everything.

snippet.textDisplay:
Dr. Rajan Sharma
Honourable President, Indian Medical Association
And All State Presidents of IMA 

Subject: Regarding the All  India Strike declared by IMA on 11th Dec, 2020

Namaskar,

I am good and hope the entire fraternity is at its best of health.

You have expressed anger for the notification of CCIM by Govt. of India, your press release pertaining to that, the protest programs given by your association, all together is giving a wrong impression of you and your association among media and public, which does not suit prominent and responsible professionals like you.
To express once opinion or oppose is welcomed in a Democracy, but for that it is necessary to study the subject deeply with various aspects, which seems to have missed by you. In this context, I feel, it will be good if you get the facts right before stepping out with any kind of protest program, certain questions and issues which I request you to give a thought.
1.) Has any of you studied the syllabus of CCIM 1979? How well informed are you about the process of admission of B. A. M. S.? Are you aware of the admission process of M.D. (Ayurved) and especially M.S. (Ayurved) and the 3 years houseman ship process? 
There is a lot of misconception spread in social media about your press release and in the name of your association. The programs declared by your association is giving wrong impression about medical fraternity in the public.
2.) You have raised a matter of MIXOPATHY (Khichdi Practice) in front of Govt. In that case, when IMA is combining with Ayush doctors, Clinics, Maternity homes and several such units, what kind of Mixopathy are you practicing. While questioning Government, have you been able to convince your colleagues from stopping practicing Mixopathy in their nursing homes?
3.) While raising concern about Quackery, instead of showing concern or challenging Govt about quacks practicing without license all over India, you are questioning working and system of constitution and regulation of Central Council of Indian Medicine and the Gazette of Govt. By doing so you are putting your own policy at question it seems!
4.) India would be proud of you if you had stood up and opposed through IMA for Medical negligence, Drug and Pharma Mafia, Financial loot by private medical Collage, Nursing Homes and Pharmaco-vigilance etc.
5.) Instead of employing nursing staff approved by Nursing Council or Paramedical Council, nursing homes or maternity homes are appointing uneducated and irrelevant staff due to which people are facing lot of problems, you could have stood up for such a cause and it would be considered a great service to the nation by you.
6.) Did you ever think, X-ray, Sonography, CT-Scan machine, Ventilator, vitals monitor, dialysis unit, surgical components, cardiograph machine or simple  B.P. Instrument stethoscope, none of them is been made by Doctors or any of IMA office bearers, they are just machines technology and you say only you can use them. Now this sounds like Colonialism! For a moment if the engineers who made these says we have made them and you are not allowed to use them, how would you take it?! Would you let it happen?! You think common man does not understand this?!  Post 11th December 2020 would you be able to handle such basic questions?!
7.) By calling Medical Integration as Mixopathy, you are hurting the intention behind integration, do you realize?!
8.) We understand other countries do not have independent medical system of their own and so there is no question of pride and prestige for them. But Indian doctors being proud of their system is far when they are not even well informed about Indian system of Medicine. Due to this lack of knowledge your fight against Govt. is knowingly – unknowingly coming up as against Ayurved.
Respected Dr. Rajan , I am attaching one of my research article along with this, which is about The Glory of Indian Surgery, especially Plastic Surgery. I request you to go through it once and let your colleagues also read the same, may be your protest will get the right direction.
This letter is purely intended to exchange thoughts and graciously remove negative aspect of the protest. Knowingly-unknowingly you have become a reason of pride for Indian system of Medicine – Ayurved, and I express my joy towards it!

Thanking you 
Ayurvedacharya, Dr Hitesh Jani,
Ex. Principal, Gujarat Ayurved University
Jamnagar

6.) Did you ever think, X-ray, Sonography, CT-Scan machine, Ventilator, vitals monitor, dialysis unit, surgical components, cardiograph machine or simple  B.P. Instrument stethoscope, none of them is been made by Doctors or any of IMA office bearers, they are just machines technology and you say only you can use them. Now this sounds like Colonialism! For a moment if the engineers who made these says we have made them and you are not allowed to use them, how would you take it?! Would you let it happen?! You think common man does not understand this?!  Post 11th December 2020 would you be able to handle such basic questions?!
7.) By calling Medical Integration as Mixopathy, you are hurting the intention behind integration, do you realize?!
8.) We understand other countries do not have independent medical system of their own and so there is no question of pride and prestige for them. But Indian doctors being proud of their system is far when they are not even well informed about Indian system of Medicine. Due to this lack of knowledge your fight against Govt. is knowingly – unknowingly coming up as against Ayurved.
Respected Dr. Rajan , I am attaching one of my research article along with this, which is about The Glory of Indian Surgery, especially Plastic Surgery. I request you to go through it once and let your colleagues also read the same, may be your protest will get the right direction.
This letter is purely intended to exchange thoughts and graciously remove negative aspect of the protest. Knowingly-unknowingly you have become a reason of pride for Indian system of Medicine – Ayurved, and I express my joy towards it!

Thanking you 
Ayurvedacharya, Dr Hitesh Jani,
Ex. Principal, Gujarat Ayurved University

snippet.textDisplay: Whereas it was nice to hear a number of your panelists come forth on market realities and dynamics. It would be unfair to say that the Indian State has no role to play and should completely insulate itself. Suppose we were to assume that the promoters had worked out a viable business model to begin with, how does, say an impartial observer hold them accountable for factors which they are in no position to control. The price of Aviation Turbine Fuel, fees for airport usage, currency exchange rate etc are not decided by market forces but by the Govt. There is nothing like a pure market, whatever economists might theorize. In real life markets are linked to society at large and socio-political circumstances.

snippet.textDisplay:
In hindsight, every  passing day also raises serious doubts that Bhushans and Jaisinghs are out with daggers to get their revenge on the SC.  Reasons:
1 A very comprehensive allegation docket which requires legal input of  high order
2 Day one leak of complaint to online media even before the 22 judges who were requested to help,   had a chance to read the complaint
3 Blatant naming of the top judicial officer so as to damage his image without even a trial in the hope of getting public sympathy for the complainant 
4 Exploiting the sensitivity attached to SH so as  to make things difficult for the court
5 Non disclosure on day one of the names of heavyweights behind the complainant like Bhushan et al. This had to come out later  following  an internal skirmish with Utsav Bain.
6 Very precise directions how the matter should be inquired into so that one of the activists can eventually take control of the process
7 walking out of the internal  process by the complainant - if it was one's own  case , described in such detail in the affidavit, then  standing interrogation shouldn't be an issue even if painful 
7 Knowing very well that  POSH and Vishaka doesn't apply in this case , yet  trying to challenge the alternative  process devised by the judges to address what is essentially an internal matter of the court
8 Not respecting the point that even though an internal inquiry was adopted , unlike in  other establishments, the people inquiring in this instance  are  judges by profession and that too senior and accomplished ones. They know as much of due process and natural justice as any of Bhushan and Jaisinghs, and more important they are trained  to look at the matter from an impartial perspective in all circumstances.. Do we doubt a doctor with our body, or a lawyer with our case, or a banker with our money? why then all this convoluted logic being peddled when trained professional judges themselves sit  in the enquiry?
9. Last,  if it is the victimisation that  really hit the complainant as claimed in some place, won't contesting on merits  the  termination of service,  been a  better  approach if one really wanted  to help the complainant? Why draw on SH which is not always to say to establish?

snippet.textDisplay:
We must amend/clarify Official Secrets Act in the light of RTI. OSA is about national security and cannot be used as a weapon to silence whistle blowers and journalists. Even national security matters should be disclosed in respect of corruption/human rights abuse as per RTI.

The first report of 2nd ARC has dealt with RTI and OSA comprehensively, and gave a practical road map to reconcile both. SARC gave specific, practical recommendations to amend law and the CCA rules. We need to make govts accountable to us; not make citizens accountable to govt.

snippet.textDisplay: The Govt keeps increasing taxes. They recently increased duty on fuel, this in turn inflates the cost of every product needed to run daily life , from FMCG products to edibles, it impacts everything, from hospitals, educational institutions, travel,  etc. And moreover citizens have started shelling huge amount of money from their pockets for something like water. More so in the southern states. There is no money left in the banks of the middle class to spend on cars or even for other essential things. Prices of things have inflated exponentially over the past few years. The Govt should not have increased the fuel prices when the crude oil prices were down in the global markets. It has caused prices of all products in the market to go up. And it has done it again with the current budget. Not sure where this is going to lead us. And there is no accountability from the politicians for the money already collected in taxes. They go on building statures and spending thousands of crores in election campaigns. PS - Also look into the balance sheets of these so called loss making petroleum companies, their net profit is in  tens and thousands of cores each year, this was the case even when the fuel prices were subsidized by the Govt and were regulated by the Govt.

snippet.textDisplay:
The present X generation and the previous one is not aware of the atrocities committed against the backward communities even during before British came to India. I urge them to see this video and clear their clouded mindset.Here only a fraction of injustice done against sc/ st and various backward communities is show but the truth is many of them were tortured very badly till death to showcase the might of the upper caste which is even prevailing now.
In school I have even experienced and seen such upper caste students make mockery when the life and teaching of Dr. B. R. Ambedkar are taught and sc/ st students are insulted about their caste. I have seen even teachers from open category, right from pre School to degree colleges condemn the philosophy and teaching of Dr. B. R Ambedkar  and openly mocking sc / st students. I have seen teachers from open category mis guide students from backward category during engineering and medical admissions.
Candidates from open category become cry babies during admission round because some underpreviledged sc / st students got admission in a prestigious course, and the open category candidate did not. The struggles of underpreviledged students is eye washed , many don't know many sc / st students come from a traditionally poor families where even have to struggle to eat a minimal square meal , leave alone getting their living and education expenses getting covered.
Even in school and colleges many sc / st students face harresment from open category students and open category teacher make sure that such cases do not get highlighted to the authorities and media.
I believe that if you want open and fair competition then please ban private coaching and classes for all which open category take advantage of to get ahead where the same cannot be afforded by students of backward categories.
Ban the management seat quota in colleges which open category takes advantage of using the back door.
I just wish the parents of the general category do not brainwash their future generations against great leaders like Dr. B. R Ambedkar because of reservation but rather try and understand the reality behind it.

snippet.textDisplay:
PMC Bank restrictions have curtailed Diwali in Maharashtra & Bombay .
Why deprive hard earned money from people and freeze their bank accounts for 6 months and permit them( account holders ) to withdraw  a paltry amount of Rs 1000/- Maximum once in a span of 6 months.
This is worse than demonetisation and preventing and curbing Indians to Celebrate their Festival Diwali.
The many curbs that have been implemented in J&K & Ladhak has spread to Maharashtra and Bombay 
Jewelry Business is on a slowdown and Zaveri Bazar looks like a Ghost Town.  
Is this our Finance Minister's Diwali Gift to the Poor & Downtrodden in Maharastra & Bombay which is part of India.
The FM has given a Hefty Gift to the Corporate Sector & The Big Business Houses on Friday, the way the Sensex behaved on Friday 20th September 2019.
The Howdy Mody campaign in Houston Texas was expensive and  must have cost at least Rs 500/- Crores to the Indian Organisers.
The 50,000 odd NRI's in Houston &  10 times more across USA & Canada will be having lavish Diwali Celebrations where as the poor Mumbhaikar's have only Rs 1000/-  to spend over 6 months which would be sufficient for One Person to buy peanuts for 100days @ Rs 10/-  and the balance 80 days drink plain water to fill their bellies.
The RBI & PMC Bank of India is under the Finance Minister of India   who has to seriously look into the issue and see that Indian Citizens are treated properly in Diwali without hardship and turmoil in Maharashtra and Bombay.

Is the EC made aware of the source of the electoral bond donors?
Why should foreign companies donate for political parties?
Who audits these party funds and its uses?
Organised crime and legalised loot of tax payers money for policy and political favours  given to corporates and its beyond any doubt.
Eligibility of a donor and their declaration of the same in their audits that are submitted to tax department and EC should be mandatory. And I think EC and SC must step in for a better transparency and accountability. It I'd about time every parliamentarians salaries and perks should be paid by their parties and not with tax payers money. 
Every reforms made is to torture the mass while the elite select and elect are benefitted.
And why are chowkidaars replacing parliamentarians?
Are we to elect chowkidaars or MPs? Any security agency can provide chowkidaars at a cheaper rate.

Convince or confuse strategy is not going to work the mass are smarter.
The wrath of the mass shall be evident in the upcoming elections.
At least I am not voting for electing any chowkidaars.
God bless all with wisdom at all times.

I have few points to raise here. First of all let me clear Allopathy is superior to Ayurveda. 
Because Allopathy took help of Physics. Ayurveda didn't. 
Physics is completely different science than Medical. So Dr. Shruti Tandon shouting at Dr. Sukumar Sardeshmukh on 29:40 is simply being arrogant here. Because the doctor only said that intensive care is physics, which is true. Right from plugging switch to electricity board, to creating electricity in the first place, supplying it to Hospital, combining it to electronics (again another branch of physics) to utilise required amount of electricity for exact purpose. So Mr. doctor you didn't study them. You took help of Physics. And that is good. That is why people trust Allopathy. Because it is quick and instant. Unlike Ayurveda. If Ayurveda also takes help of Physics, then may be who knows they can also do wonder. 
The quantum physics that revealed the nature in smallest minute possible state has lead to the discovery of cancer treatment like radiology. Then control of radiation to treat exact cancer tumour goes to field of electronics. The field of electronics has developed the science of using switches to control beam of radiation in required amount just using our finger tips. These are credits of engineers and physicists, which the doctor tried to take credit to herself by saying she had also studied physics, no you didn't. Physics is not what you have studied up to class 12th, 12th physics is like elementary physics. And what you have studied in medical is application of these physics inventions, just like in ITI students learn applications of various machines. 

The years of experiment of scientists like Max Planck, or deBroglie or Einstein or Tesla and etc has today direct implementation on Medical science. If Ayurveda also takes help of Physics and amalgamate into their field of work, it will be gain for humanity.

The doctors acting like an uneducated fool here, just like Baba Ram Dev, who doesn't have understanding of medical sciences. 

In fact this conversation you are having is because of various fields of physics working in unison. Even the screens available in medical field showing different graphs are product of electronics. You are only utilising in medical field. Again it is a good thing. When someone reminds you that, and if you get angry, this means these Allopathy doctors considers them as supreme, otherwise why you would you get angry. The Ayurvedic doctor raised a very good question that taking help of Physics (light, energy) than claiming it is intrinsic superiority of allopathy over Ayurveda is ignorance.

snippet.textDisplay:
SAD,SAD , utterly decived are the citizens of this country by the government who they voted with such great faith,hope & enthusiasm . Today they are made to starve for their support , and moreover lied to , telling the people who are starving that they are not starving, telling those who have lost their jobs that they have not lost their jobs , telling those whose business are going down that their business is doing fine , telling the farmers that their loans can not be forgiven but forgiving the loans of mega business houses . 
 The farmer has to sell his land to clear his loan & then starve to death or commit suicide , whereas the mega business houses can dispose of their assets clear their dues & still survive . SAD, SAD , BAD ! GOD HELP WE INDIANS WHO ARE BEARING ALL THIS WITHOUT COMPLAINING !!! 
  BUT FOR HOW LONG ? 
  Economy can crumble in no time , but , to build it up again will take decades . Dosent anyone understand this ? Specially the responsible / irreparable governments . & I think that every citizen should wake up & start questioning  those responsible . 
  Not very far back the developed countries were worried that INDIA will overtake them economically and now they are relived of that worry . It will take us 10 years to come back to where we stood and another 10 years to cover up for those 10 years. 
 Let us all pray that BHARATH MATA will pull us out of this socio economic mess we have put ourselves in.
 JAI HIND-- JAI BHARATH-- BHARATH MATA KE JAI .

snippet.textDisplay:
One of the biggest issues before the people,  which has not got the attention it deserves, is Prime Minister Modi's growing megalomania. 
 
If a PM of any other parliamentary democracy went to the polls with hardly any of his top aides contesting elections for the Lower House, people would laugh. In India, bhakts are fine with Mr. Modi downsizing any of his cabinet ministers who he thinks could be a threat to him. The usual practice is to have them elected to the Rajya Sabha so that they cannot build up a base among the people. Apart from Nitin Gadkari (who has the back of the RSS), Rajnath Singh and a few others, hardly any of the BJP top brass are facing the people this time. Uber loyal Amit Shah gets the safe seat of Gandhi Nagar, though.

Foreign minister- not Contesting
Finance minister-not contesting
Defense minister-not contesting
Rail min- not contesting
Oil/Gas min- not contesting
Coal min- not contesting
HRD-not contesting
Speaker - not contesting.

The great man has also taken to referring to himself in the third person. An analysis by another channel of 35 of Mr. Modi's recent speeches shows that the most common word he uses is Modi.

The BJP manifesto is pathetic .

Nothing is being talked about improving the quality of goods being produced in India to meet international quality standards , SMART CITIES , BRINGING BACK BLACK MONEY FROM SWISS BANKS , raising the quality of education in  rural and district level schools , bringing agriculture into the formal sector , petrol price , rupee Vs dollar exchange rate , tackling brain drain , improving and raising to international standards the infrastructure in India , and the creation of FORMAL SECTOR JOBS. 
All they ve spoken is of national security , some social structural changes ( UCC , Article 35A , etc) , doubling the income of farmers ( but they have not told us as to how they will achieve that ) , where's development ?

If these are achieved , India would be developed .

Allocate days for each state (eg Bihar)  with all the infrastructure catering to that state .
Push the largest groups  through the concentrated infrastructure first.
Do not keep the largest groups in camps.  Facilitate their movement concentrating all infrastructure immediately.
